name: DataBarConditionalFormat
description: Represents an Excel Conditional Data Bar Type.

properties.name: showDataBarOnly
properties.description: If true, hides the values from the cells where the data bar is applied.

properties.name: axisFormat
properties.description: Representation of how the axis is determined for an Excel data bar.

properties.name: axisColor
properties.description: HTML color code representing the color of the Axis line, of the form #RRGGBB (e.g. "FFA500") or as a named HTML color (e.g. "orange").

properties.name: barDirection
properties.description: Represents the direction that the data bar graphic should be based on.

properties.name: positiveFormat
properties.description: Representation of all values to the right of the axis in an Excel data bar.

properties.name: negativeFormat
properties.description: Representation of all values to the left of the axis in an Excel data bar.

properties.name: lowerBoundRule
properties.description: The rule for what consistutes the lower bound (and how to calculate it, if applicable) for a data bar.

properties.name: upperBoundRule
properties.description: The rule for what constitutes the upper bound (and how to calculate it, if applicable) for a data bar.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
